                    <!-- hightlights end -->
                    <div class="font-light">
                        <p>The Everest Base Camp Trek is one of the most legendary trekking adventures in the world,
                            offering a rare opportunity to walk in the shadow of Mount Everest (8,848.86m). Nestled in
                            the
                            breathtaking Himalayas of Nepal, this journey combines dramatic mountain scenery, rich
                            Sherpa
                            culture, and a deep sense of personal achievement.</p><br>
                        <p>The adventure begins in Kathmandu, followed by a thrilling mountain flight to Lukla often
                            considered one of the most exciting runways in the world. From here, the trail winds through
                            overgrown forests, suspension bridges draped with prayer flags, and charming Sherpa
                            settlements
                            like Namche Bazaar, the vibrant gateway to the Everest region.</p><br>
                        <p>As you ascend deeper into the Khumbu region, the landscape transforms dramatically from green
                            valleys to alpine terrain and glacial rubble. Along the way, trekkers encounter ancient
                            monasteries such as Tengboche, spinning prayer wheels, and warm hospitality that reflects
                            the
                            spiritual and cultural richness of the Himalayas.</p><br>
                        <p>Reaching Everest Base Camp (5,364m) is a moment of pure accomplishment. Standing at the foot
                            of
                            the world’s highest peak, surrounded by towering giants and the Khumbu Glacier, is both
                            humbling
                            and unforgettable. Another highlight is the early morning hike to Kala Patthar (5,545m),
                            widely
                            regarded as the best vantage point for panoramic views of Everest and the surrounding peaks.
                            Despite its global reputation, the trek is non-technical and suitable for determined
                            beginners
                            with a good level of fitness. The main challenge is altitude, which is why the itinerary
                            includes carefully planned acclimatization days to ensure safety and enjoyment.</p><br>
                        <p>Beyond the physical journey, the Everest Base Camp Trek is an emotional and cultural
                            experience
                            connecting you with nature, local traditions, and your own limits. Whether it’s the sound of
                            prayer flags fluttering in the wind, the sight of snow capped peaks at sunrise, or the
                            friendship built along the trail, every moment becomes part of a story you’ll carry for
                            life.
                        </p>
